SIMPLE: infinitesimal
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Infinitesimal
<hw>In`fin*i*tes"i*mal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>infinit⟦eacute⟧simal</ets>, fr. <ets>infinit⟦eacute⟧sime</ets>
infinitely small, fr. L. <ets>infinitus</ets>. See <er>Infinite</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>Infinitely or indefinitely small; less than
any assignable quantity or value; very small.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Infinitesimal calculus</b></col>, <cd>the different and
the integral calculus, when developed according to the method used by
Leibnitz, who regarded the increments given to variables as
infinitesimal.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infinitesimal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Infinitesimal
<hw>In`fin*i*tes"i*mal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>An
infinitely small quantity; that which is less than any assignable
quantity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infinitesimally</ent>⟦br⟧
